org.flossware.jcore.collections.map

Interface FunctionalMap<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Map<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFunctionalMap, DefaultFunctionalMap

    public interface FunctionalMap<K,V>
extends Map<K,V>
    Represents a "functional" map which allows us to extend the core functions with values that return self so we can chain calls. Similar to what one can do with StringBuilder. For example: functionalMap.putF("1", "2").putF("3", "4")
    Author:
    sfloess
